President Barack Obama will award Dakota Meyer, a former Marine Corps Corporal, the Medal of Honor for his actions while serving in Afghanistan in 2009. Meyer will be the third living recipient and first Marine to receive the Medal of Honor for actions in Iraq or Afghanistan. He will be honored for his courageous and selfless service. Meyer enlisted in the Marine Corps in 2006 and completed his active duty commitment in 2010. He currently serves in the Inactive Ready Reserve of the Marine Corps Reserve. Throughout his military career, Meyer deployed to both Iraq and Afghanistan. His decorations include the Purple Heart Medal, Navy and Marine Corps Commendation Medal, and Good Conduct Medal, among others. The Medal of Honor is awarded to members of the Armed Forces who display exceptional gallantry and self-sacrifice in combat.